.TH "freezing_slow_path" 9 "freezing_slow_path" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
freezing_slow_path \- slow path for testing whether a task needs to be frozen
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" freezing_slow_path
.BI "(struct task_struct *p "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "p" 12
task to be tested
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
This function is called by \fBfreezing\fP if system_freezing_cnt isn't zero
and tests whether \fIp\fP needs to enter and stay in frozen state.  Can be
called under any context.  The freezers are responsible for ensuring the
target tasks see the updated state.
